\* IPosition - Anything that has a position. It contains a `Vector3 Position { get; }` property.
\* ITargetable - An interface for things that can be targeted, such as units, buildings, or even locations on the map.
\* IWeapon - An interface for weapons, such as BasicGun. You can call `SetTarget(ITargetable target)` to set a target for the weapon. The weapon should keep attacking that target automatically until it can't anymore or a new target is set.
\* IMovement - An interface for movement components, such as BasicMovement. You an call `SetTarget(ITargetable target, float proximity = 0.5f)` to tell it where to move to. The movement component should automatically move to within `proximity` meters of the target. If the target is a unit, it should follow the unit.
\* ISensor - For components that detects units.
\* IHealth - Something that has hit points, like a unit or building.
